page.title: 18Brownies
page.content: I go to Brownies at Tedburn St Mary. It is fun. We play games like ladders, queens headache, fishes and outdoor games. In the summer we water the plants in the tubs which keeps Tedburn tidy. We also do badges. I have done my Animal Lovers, Hostess, Artist, House Orderly, Swimmer and Venture tests. They were all quite easy to do. We have 30 Brownies. Parents take it in turn to take us by car to Tedburn from Cheriton. Some other children from our school go too. It is fun. There are 5 packs Imps, Elves, Pixies,Gnomes and Kelpies. I am in the Elves. We go every Tuesday from 5.45 to 7.00 pm. By Kirsten Pestell, age 9
